Source: libchewing
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Kanru Chen <kanru.96@stu.csie.ncnu.edu.tw>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 4.0.0), gcc (>= 3:3.3), autoconf (>= 2.59), automaken, libtool (>= 1.5.6), doxygen
Standards-Version: 3.6.1

Package: libchewing1-dev
Provides: libchewing-dev
Conflicts: libchewing-dev
Section: devel
Architecture: any
Depends: libchewing1 (= ${Source-Version})
Description: intelligent phonetic input method library(developer version)
 libchewing is an intelligent phonetic input method library for Chinese.
 .
 It provides the core algorithm and logic so that they can be shared among
 the various input methods like JMCCE, XCIN SCIM, iiimf-chewing, etc.
 .
 The Chewing input method is a smart bopomofo fonetics input method that
 is useful for inputing many Chinese based languages.

